 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\nf(x) find the maximum point of f, given that x &lt;= k<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\nconstrained maximization<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"3c9dc6fad7bbe9477e0a50832a6e125f2eacb6fa","tid":302174,"uid":9187,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T01:28:12.000Z","msg":"嚇走哂d 18dse啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"7196218d34d51cf47868032c0e4fbf4e5f5cf3f2","tid":302174,"uid":9187,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T01:29:22.000Z","msg":"[dse level] <br />\nOpportunity cost is the highest-valued option forgone. Why &quot;highest&quot;?<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"293650de069e9bf92a275e48eec724cdf20bac92","tid":302174,"uid":1788,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T06:30:21.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>[dse level] <br />\nOpportunity cost is the highest-valued option forgone. Why &quot;highest&quot;?<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\nA rational person will not choose the &quot;non-highest&quot; options even if they do not pursue the chosen option. In other words, one can only get back the value of the highest valued option forgone when they do not pursue chosen event. Therefore, only the option which has the highest value is irrelevant to decision making, thus is the opportunity cost."},{"pid":"a84dbe501ad750705c7f995b5f47dc099eadb7c2","tid":302174,"uid":1788,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T06:30:57.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>[dse level] <br />\nOpportunity cost is the highest-valued option forgone. Why &quot;highest&quot;?<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\nA rational person will not choose the &quot;non-highest&quot; options even if they do not pursue the chosen option. In other words, one can only get back the value of the highest valued option forgone when they do not pursue chosen event. Therefore, only the forgone option which has the highest value is relevant to decision making, thus is the opportunity cost.</blockquote><br />\n***"},{"pid":"d7246b1ad19c462866d3bac5a86a4cbac63cdc6d","tid":302174,"uid":1788,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T06:31:45.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote><blockquote>[dse level] <br />\nOpportunity cost is the highest-valued option forgone. Why &quot;highest&quot;?<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\nA rational person will not choose the &quot;non-highest&quot; <span style=\"color: red;\">firgone </span>options even if they do not pursue the chosen option. In other words, one can only get back the value of the highest valued option forgone when they do not pursue chosen event. Therefore, only the forgone option which has the highest value is relevant to decision making, thus is the opportunity cost.</blockquote><br />\n***</blockquote><br />\n打錯哂<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a6811ba15de9893f299f2e5a274492866c0d295f","tid":302174,"uid":1788,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T06:32:12.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote><blockquote>[dse level] <br />\nOpportunity cost is the highest-valued option forgone. Why &quot;highest&quot;?<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\nA rational person will not choose the &quot;non-highest&quot; <span style=\"color: red;\">forgone </span>options even if they do not pursue the chosen option. In other words, one can only get back the value of the highest valued option forgone when they do not pursue chosen event. Therefore, only the forgone option which has the highest value is relevant to decision making, thus is the opportunity cost.</blockquote><br />\n***</blockquote><br />\n打錯哂<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f80fc44c2248c55f4504bb888d74a0ff71d6e16f","tid":302174,"uid":102260,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T06:38:33.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote>U is a function of revision time in econ (t)<br />\nmax U s.t. t &lt;= (days remaining)<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n你計一次<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\">3014 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> </span><br />\n3113<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/love.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n留名成班都唔識<br />\n如果佢唔教/tutorial 唔講既</blockquote><br />\n你會唔識?<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n我睇唔明你上面個句<img src=\"/asset